1
00:00:48,423 --> 00:00:50,467
I have to cover your face now.

2
00:00:54,637 --> 00:00:56,306
What is it? What are you doing?

3
00:00:58,349 --> 00:01:00,018
I can't talk now.

4
00:01:00,810 --> 00:01:02,729
-Talk about yourself.
-What?

5
00:01:02,812 --> 00:01:04,147
Just tell me about you.

6
00:01:10,904 --> 00:01:12,072
I'm...

7
00:01:14,699 --> 00:01:15,950
Well, did I

8
00:01:18,411 --> 00:01:22,040
like documentaries
because they were vivid?

9
00:01:23,666 --> 00:01:25,293
Things that flow by.

10
00:01:25,668 --> 00:01:27,086
Animate creatures.

11
00:01:29,339 --> 00:01:31,508
Did I think that capturing these things

12
00:01:31,841 --> 00:01:33,676
with a camera was the highlight

13
00:01:34,135 --> 00:01:35,136
of documentaries?

14
00:01:36,054 --> 00:01:39,849
Why can't I remember
my old self in the past?

15
00:01:39,974 --> 00:01:41,309
In the past? When?

16
00:01:41,601 --> 00:01:42,811
What?

17
00:01:46,481 --> 00:01:47,565
The past.

18
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:50,443
When was that?

19
00:01:51,277 --> 00:01:52,320
The past.

20
00:01:55,532 --> 00:01:58,618
When we met, what kind of person was I?

21
00:02:00,912 --> 00:02:02,038
Me?

22
00:02:06,417 --> 00:02:07,544
Is that so?

23
00:02:09,921 --> 00:02:11,339
I don't remember

24
00:02:12,924 --> 00:02:14,342
how I used to be.

25
00:03:35,256 --> 00:03:36,966
Please remember me.

26
00:03:37,884 --> 00:03:39,344
Not just who I am.

27
00:03:40,178 --> 00:03:42,013
Remember how I was happy with you.

28
00:03:43,973 --> 00:03:45,433
If you're not here,

29
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:48,228
who would remember how happy I was, then?

30
00:04:00,406 --> 00:04:02,533
Sometimes the space I exist in

31
00:04:02,784 --> 00:04:05,536
feels smaller than my body.

32
00:04:07,372 --> 00:04:11,417
It hurts as if I crush my body
to fit in that space

33
00:04:11,584 --> 00:04:14,087
and put it back in.

34
00:04:14,587 --> 00:04:16,172
That's how

35
00:04:16,422 --> 00:04:19,217
I barely breathe in the space.

36
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:23,429
That's how I have to hold out.

37
00:04:24,555 --> 00:04:26,474
Because I have to remember you.

38
00:04:27,892 --> 00:04:29,102
You're...

39
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:33,690
Yes. You're so mean.

40
00:04:59,716 --> 00:05:01,968
Let me do it. You should go to work.

41
00:05:04,887 --> 00:05:06,014
It's okay.

42
00:05:06,723 --> 00:05:09,892
-Want something to eat?
-No, I'll eat by myself.

43
00:05:10,101 --> 00:05:11,352
It's okay.

44
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:15,273
Aren't you late for work?

45
00:05:16,441 --> 00:05:17,317
No.

46
00:06:03,029 --> 00:06:04,113
Hey, Director Kim.

47
00:06:04,655 --> 00:06:05,490
Yes, sir.

48
00:06:05,573 --> 00:06:08,951
I just wanted to call you that.
You're a director now.

49
00:06:09,118 --> 00:06:10,912
-Director Kim.
-Director Kim.

50
00:06:10,995 --> 00:06:14,415
-Director Kim Hwan-dong.
-Gosh, please stop it.

51
00:06:14,499 --> 00:06:15,333
I sense...

52
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:16,959
power.

53
00:06:17,043 --> 00:06:20,463
What you just said is supposed to
sound like "Gosh, please stop it."

54
00:06:21,172 --> 00:06:22,006
"Please stop it."

55
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:23,883
I sense great power. You're the director.

56
00:06:25,676 --> 00:06:26,636
But...

57
00:06:29,639 --> 00:06:32,558
-Why do you seem to like it?
-What? Like what?

58
00:06:32,642 --> 00:06:34,727
Why are you happy

59
00:06:35,645 --> 00:06:36,771
that I'm gone?

60
00:06:43,945 --> 00:06:44,904
I sense great power.

61
00:06:44,987 --> 00:06:48,950
That one was supposed to sound like
"Why are you happy that I'm gone?"

62
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:50,743
-This is you.
-Charisma.

63
00:06:50,827 --> 00:06:52,537
"Why are you happy that I'm gone?"

64
00:06:52,620 --> 00:06:54,122
When did I say that?

65
00:06:54,205 --> 00:06:55,456
I sense great power within you.

66
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:57,542
You're the director, indeed.

67
00:07:05,842 --> 00:07:06,884
"Charisma."

68
00:07:07,844 --> 00:07:08,845
"I sense great power."

69
00:07:09,762 --> 00:07:10,888
Have some tofu, Director Kim.

70
00:07:17,728 --> 00:07:20,231
The Fengshui of the building
must suck like hell.

71
00:07:21,023 --> 00:07:22,984
Hey, let's go get some smoothies.

72
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:24,110
It's on him.

73
00:07:24,527 --> 00:07:25,945
I quit after-meal drinks.

74
00:07:26,028 --> 00:07:28,030
Then don't get one.
You can still treat us.

75
00:07:28,573 --> 00:07:31,242
Is there any weakness of me
that makes me do that?

76
00:07:31,951 --> 00:07:35,496
We've bought you a lot of drinks.
That's your weakness.

77
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:39,417
Now it's time for you to buy us some.

78
00:07:39,709 --> 00:07:41,169
Maybe it's time I got a new job.

79
00:07:41,252 --> 00:07:42,503
No one will offer you a job anyway.

80
00:07:42,587 --> 00:07:44,464
I don't mind going to a place
where I'm not wanted.

81
00:07:46,507 --> 00:07:47,425
Well,

82
00:07:47,508 --> 00:07:50,261
I need to go to Ms. Jung's office.
I should get going now.

83
00:07:50,344 --> 00:07:53,556
-What? Okay.
-See you?

84
00:07:54,223 --> 00:07:57,059
Again? Does that place have
the latest massage chair or something?

85
00:07:57,143 --> 00:07:58,311
Why does he go there every day?

86
00:07:58,394 --> 00:08:01,647
He's going overboard on it.
I heard he doesn't even sleep.

87
00:08:02,231 --> 00:08:04,358
The script review is
longer than the project proposal.

88
00:08:04,442 --> 00:08:06,068
Is it even possible?

89
00:08:06,152 --> 00:08:08,571
And he writes more
than the assistant writer does.

90
00:08:08,905 --> 00:08:10,948
He's a nutcase. Is he really jealous?

91
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:13,409
-What?
-What? Nothing.

92
00:08:13,534 --> 00:08:15,703
You should be his pacemaker.

93
00:08:15,995 --> 00:08:17,830
He shouldn't get exhausted
in the beginning.

94
00:08:17,997 --> 00:08:19,957
That's what I did when I made my debut.

95
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:23,586
This isn't nothing like that.
I heard he already scouted Mr. Yang.

96
00:08:24,670 --> 00:08:26,297
Mr. Yang? The director of photography?

97
00:08:26,380 --> 00:08:27,256
Yes.

98
00:08:28,132 --> 00:08:30,593
What? He's mine.

99
00:08:30,676 --> 00:08:34,222
Interception. He even intercepts
his boss's DOP. How charismatic.

100
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:54,283
Hey, Mr. Son.

101
00:08:54,492 --> 00:08:57,703
-Hey, Mr. Yang.
-What are you doing in my studio?

102
00:08:57,787 --> 00:08:58,913
What's up?

103
00:08:58,996 --> 00:09:00,831
Nothing. I just live nearby.

104
00:09:00,915 --> 00:09:02,708
-Do you not live in Sangam?
-Yes, I do.

105
00:09:02,792 --> 00:09:04,627
Sangam is not close to Paju.

106
00:09:05,336 --> 00:09:07,964
It's a small country. I can say it's close
as long as I can get here by bus.

107
00:09:08,130 --> 00:09:09,340
Fine then.

108
00:09:10,049 --> 00:09:11,884
Grab a meal before you go.
We have good catering.

109
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:13,886
I'm good, thanks.

110
00:09:14,595 --> 00:09:16,013
So, about your next project.

111
00:09:16,138 --> 00:09:17,098
Did you

112
00:09:17,932 --> 00:09:18,849
make any plans?

113
00:09:20,017 --> 00:09:22,770
I'm working with Hwan-dong.
I thought he told you about it.

114
00:09:22,979 --> 00:09:24,021
Oh, right.

115
00:09:24,522 --> 00:09:26,107
I did tell him to ask you.

116
00:09:26,190 --> 00:09:29,026
Sure. I should look out for him
since it's his first project.

117
00:09:29,402 --> 00:09:30,987
So when does your project start?

118
00:09:31,070 --> 00:09:32,947
Mine? It would begin

119
00:09:34,365 --> 00:09:35,533
around the same time.

120
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:37,660
Really?

121
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:41,622
So Mr. Cheon is
not working with you either.

122
00:09:41,706 --> 00:09:43,332
Mr. Cheon, The art director?

123
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:45,876
-And Music Director Kim Tae-seong.
-Even Mr. Kim, the music director?

124
00:09:46,877 --> 00:09:49,463
I really didn't know you cared
about your junior that much.

125
00:09:49,839 --> 00:09:50,756
You're amazing.

126
00:09:52,717 --> 00:09:55,636
I mean it's Hwan-dong's debut
we're talking about.

127
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:58,014
You're really cool. Look at you.

128
00:09:58,598 --> 00:10:00,725
-No, I'm not.
-You go, man.

129
00:10:08,608 --> 00:10:10,401
CHEON DAE-SEONG, 43 YEARS OLD
ART DIRECTOR

130
00:10:43,726 --> 00:10:46,771
-So this is why you're here.
-I'm sorry.

131
00:10:49,398 --> 00:10:50,483
I'm really sorry.

132
00:10:50,816 --> 00:10:53,110
It's okay. The one next to it
is expensive. Try breaking that one.

133
00:11:07,792 --> 00:11:09,919
-It slipped.
-What's your problem? Just say it.

134
00:11:10,002 --> 00:11:11,003
It just slipped.

135
00:11:11,087 --> 00:11:14,006
No, it didn't.
I saw flick your wrist just now.

136
00:11:16,133 --> 00:11:17,718
-Don't do it.
-You signed the contract.

137
00:11:17,802 --> 00:11:19,136
-I'm sorry.
-How could you?

138
00:11:28,979 --> 00:11:32,316
KIM TAE-SEONG, 39 YEARS OLD
MUSIC DIRECTOR

139
00:11:54,171 --> 00:11:55,005
Well?

140
00:11:58,717 --> 00:11:59,677
Well...

141
00:12:00,928 --> 00:12:03,973
This is Hwan-dong's debut.
We should look out for him.

142
00:12:04,056 --> 00:12:06,642
The directors I work with are
the best in the industry.

143
00:12:06,725 --> 00:12:09,145
You don't mind if I play cool
like this, do you?

144
00:12:09,228 --> 00:12:10,062
No.

145
00:12:11,147 --> 00:12:13,649
Right. I was thinking
that I'm a very cool person,

146
00:12:13,732 --> 00:12:17,069
but then I came to think
that you might be worried about it.

147
00:12:17,528 --> 00:12:18,821
No. You don't have to mind me.

148
00:12:19,238 --> 00:12:21,031
I knew it. You're very generous.

149
00:12:21,157 --> 00:12:23,075
Even though they are the best directors,

150
00:12:23,159 --> 00:12:26,537
but the staff members we will work with
are just as good. Don't worry.

151
00:12:26,704 --> 00:12:27,955
I told you, I'm not worried.

152
00:12:32,042 --> 00:12:34,170
Aren't you supposed
to be a little worried though?

153
00:12:35,129 --> 00:12:37,840
Well... Why should I
worry about stuff like that?

154
00:12:38,048 --> 00:12:39,550
-Because you're the writer.
-My point.

155
00:12:39,717 --> 00:12:40,551
I get it.

156
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:43,095
You write the script,
but you won't be directing it.

157
00:12:43,179 --> 00:12:45,598
So you want to draw a line
and only care about your side of the job.

158
00:12:46,015 --> 00:12:46,891
Is that what you mean?

159
00:12:46,974 --> 00:12:50,311
You just told me not to worry about it.
Why are you upset that I'm not worried?

160
00:12:50,394 --> 00:12:52,146
I don't know. It's just that

161
00:12:52,646 --> 00:12:54,565
seeing you being so nonchalant
bothers me somehow.

162
00:12:54,648 --> 00:12:55,774
Why aren't you worried?

163
00:12:56,150 --> 00:12:57,568
Because our director is Son Beom-su.

164
00:13:00,112 --> 00:13:02,740
-Let's go. I need to go see my office.
-Okay.

165
00:13:06,660 --> 00:13:09,288
-Why?
-Don't get cold feet just because

166
00:13:09,371 --> 00:13:10,331
you lost your staff to him.

167
00:13:10,581 --> 00:13:12,208
I just let them work with him
because I'm cool.

168
00:13:12,374 --> 00:13:13,959
Okay. Let's just go.

169
00:13:16,837 --> 00:13:18,506
I'm totally fine with this.

170
00:13:43,155 --> 00:13:44,823
What's... What's wrong?

171
00:13:45,533 --> 00:13:46,575
What?

172
00:13:49,745 --> 00:13:50,913
-What?
-Well...

173
00:13:51,580 --> 00:13:52,748
You seem to be staring at me.

174
00:13:52,957 --> 00:13:54,917
-No, I'm not.
-Okay.

175
00:13:56,794 --> 00:13:57,962
Is everything going well?

176
00:13:58,128 --> 00:14:00,130
Yes. I'm working hard.

177
00:14:00,297 --> 00:14:02,174
You should pace yourself. Take your time.

178
00:14:02,424 --> 00:14:03,342
Okay.

179
00:14:03,884 --> 00:14:05,886
But you know, I just can't help it.

180
00:14:05,970 --> 00:14:07,721
I guess this is just who I am.

181
00:14:08,013 --> 00:14:09,765
So this is just who you really are.

182
00:14:12,768 --> 00:14:14,812
Right. It is.

183
00:14:18,232 --> 00:14:19,316
I guess you can't help it.

184
00:14:22,027 --> 00:14:22,945
Keep going.

185
00:14:23,988 --> 00:14:24,989
Okay.

186
00:14:38,335 --> 00:14:40,588
Ta-da.

187
00:14:43,549 --> 00:14:45,509
It's just the right size.

188
00:14:45,593 --> 00:14:47,595
It has a nice view, and it's quiet.

189
00:14:47,678 --> 00:14:49,346
The passcode to the door lock is 1004.

190
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:51,849
You can read the manual
and change it if you want, Ms. Lim.

191
00:14:51,932 --> 00:14:52,766
Okay.

192
00:14:53,475 --> 00:14:55,019
And this is the bathroom.

193
00:14:56,729 --> 00:14:57,813
Hello.

194
00:14:59,523 --> 00:15:00,941
What's wrong, Ms. General Manager?

195
00:15:01,650 --> 00:15:02,735
Your arms...

196
00:15:03,819 --> 00:15:05,696
They're ripped.

197
00:15:08,866 --> 00:15:11,035
Han-ju's heart, attention. At ease!

198
00:15:11,744 --> 00:15:12,786
Attention.

199
00:15:13,454 --> 00:15:16,165
I heard Ms. Lim doesn't
like fluorescent lights.

200
00:15:16,457 --> 00:15:17,666
Go on, try it.

201
00:15:21,378 --> 00:15:22,588
Shoot, I just remembered.

202
00:15:22,671 --> 00:15:24,715
They told me the ventilator was broken.

203
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:26,800
No. We can just replace it with a new one.

204
00:15:26,884 --> 00:15:28,093
So I brought the tools.

205
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:30,220
You're quite the technician today.

206
00:15:30,429 --> 00:15:32,598
It's just something that anyone can do.

207
00:15:32,765 --> 00:15:33,933
Thank you.

208
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:39,730
Right. There's going to be a bed in here.

209
00:15:39,897 --> 00:15:41,357
The bed is being delivered today.

210
00:15:42,983 --> 00:15:45,903
If the room is too small,
you can work in the living room.

211
00:15:45,986 --> 00:15:48,489
-We will put a dining table here.
-Okay.

212
00:15:48,739 --> 00:15:50,574
That's also being delivered today.

213
00:16:01,835 --> 00:16:03,170
I don't want you

214
00:16:03,337 --> 00:16:05,089
to watch the TV for too long, Ms. Lim.

215
00:16:06,465 --> 00:16:08,092
If you stay here for too long,

216
00:16:09,301 --> 00:16:12,096
I won't get to see
my friend Jin-joo much at home.

217
00:16:13,222 --> 00:16:14,390
My gosh.

218
00:16:14,848 --> 00:16:17,017
How can you be so cute?

219
00:16:17,309 --> 00:16:18,644
I just can't be mad at you.

220
00:16:18,936 --> 00:16:19,937
I love you.

221
00:16:22,231 --> 00:16:23,607
It doesn't matter anyway.

222
00:16:24,650 --> 00:16:27,277
I'm finally getting my own office.

223
00:16:28,570 --> 00:16:31,365
I just want to enjoy this for now.

224
00:16:31,448 --> 00:16:32,783
I won't think about anything else.

225
00:16:34,118 --> 00:16:36,120
My very first office.

226
00:16:48,173 --> 00:16:49,466
I'm proud of you.

227
00:16:50,551 --> 00:16:51,510
You look so mature.

228
00:16:52,052 --> 00:16:54,513
-That's not true.
-I mean you're cool.

229
00:16:56,015 --> 00:16:58,267
Gosh, this is nice.

230
00:17:00,060 --> 00:17:02,271
I won't let anyone touch my place.

231
00:17:03,897 --> 00:17:05,315
My silent

232
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,694
and cozy office.

233
00:17:13,866 --> 00:17:15,159
It tastes good.

234
00:17:17,745 --> 00:17:19,329
Gosh, what did you do?

235
00:17:19,413 --> 00:17:22,166
-You should've flipped it.
-That's your job, Mom.

236
00:17:22,249 --> 00:17:24,334
I invited all the people I know.

237
00:17:25,127 --> 00:17:27,296
This is a party.

238
00:17:31,759 --> 00:17:32,801
"You know what?

239
00:17:32,885 --> 00:17:35,888
My daughter became a writer."

240
00:17:37,139 --> 00:17:38,307
I called everyone.

241
00:17:44,104 --> 00:17:46,565
-You can't cast her.
-Why not? She's popular.

242
00:17:46,648 --> 00:17:48,317
I know she's popular.

243
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:50,402
But she's not good enough
to play a lead role yet.

244
00:17:50,486 --> 00:17:52,029
We need someone new.

245
00:17:52,112 --> 00:17:53,739
She's been getting
a lot of scripts these days.

246
00:17:53,906 --> 00:17:55,616
We should cast her
before she becomes too famous.

247
00:17:55,699 --> 00:17:57,117
But not the lead role.

248
00:17:57,201 --> 00:17:58,577
Why would you risk that?

249
00:17:58,660 --> 00:18:00,662
Can't you just trust me on this
like you did on the deal?

250
00:18:00,746 --> 00:18:02,289
Why the need for such a lame conflict?

251
00:18:02,372 --> 00:18:04,249
You're working with a budding writer,

252
00:18:04,541 --> 00:18:06,376
and the format is different from
existing dramas.

253
00:18:06,710 --> 00:18:08,170
We're already taking a lot of risks here.

254
00:18:08,253 --> 00:18:09,755
You should compromise at least a little.

255
00:18:09,838 --> 00:18:11,548
We can't let a rookie actress
play the lead role.

256
00:18:11,632 --> 00:18:14,593
How much do you think
a top star can guarantee high ratings?

257
00:18:14,676 --> 00:18:16,929
Is zero reaction on your trailer videos
what you want?

258
00:18:18,013 --> 00:18:20,224
-It has to be someone famous.
-There's a good example.

259
00:18:20,682 --> 00:18:22,017
Think about the Reply series.

260
00:18:22,101 --> 00:18:24,144
I don't care if it's Reply
or Forward, a no is a no.

261
00:18:24,228 --> 00:18:26,730
