628
00:42:46,605 --> 00:42:49,024
-Kim Hwan-dong?
-He's very gentle,

629
00:42:49,108 --> 00:42:51,735
kind of cute, and hardworking.
But he's a lunatic.

630
00:42:51,819 --> 00:42:53,445
He's all good, but he's a lunatic?

631
00:42:53,529 --> 00:42:55,698
He writes more than
the three of us put together.

632
00:42:55,781 --> 00:42:57,616
And he comes up with more ideas
than the three of us.

633
00:42:57,700 --> 00:43:00,619
He's very kind, and he smiles a lot.

634
00:43:00,703 --> 00:43:02,246
But he turns into Trump at a meeting.

635
00:43:02,329 --> 00:43:03,706
He's not scared of anything.

636
00:43:03,789 --> 00:43:06,709
-He's a little like that.
-What?

637
00:43:08,210 --> 00:43:10,129
Nothing. Directors are always like that.

638
00:43:10,212 --> 00:43:12,423
He's not like other directors.

639
00:43:12,506 --> 00:43:16,260
It's like he's trying to take revenge.

640
00:43:16,343 --> 00:43:17,636
Exactly. He's different.

641
00:43:17,720 --> 00:43:21,098
He's full of desire for success.

642
00:43:21,640 --> 00:43:23,267
But there's a story behind it.

643
00:43:23,350 --> 00:43:26,478
My point. He's with
three experienced writers.

644
00:43:26,562 --> 00:43:29,106
We've evolved to see things
that we don't even want to see.

645
00:43:29,189 --> 00:43:32,610
I'm pretty sure his ex-girlfriend...

646
00:43:34,236 --> 00:43:36,238
-married a rich guy.
-I'm sure that's what it is.

647
00:43:36,322 --> 00:43:37,615
He just can't fool us.

648
00:43:37,698 --> 00:43:40,367
It's so obvious
that you are drama writers.

649
00:43:40,701 --> 00:43:44,330
Hey, what a director does
definitely depends on the writer.

650
00:43:44,413 --> 00:43:45,581
You should train him well.

651
00:43:45,664 --> 00:43:48,083
The existence of this world is objective.

652
00:43:48,167 --> 00:43:50,461
It's not something you can change
with subjective efforts.

653
00:43:50,544 --> 00:43:53,005
Right. Directors can never be trained.

654
00:43:53,088 --> 00:43:55,257
I'm not just a typical writer though.

655
00:43:57,801 --> 00:43:59,845
Then this is where we give you a mission.

656
00:43:59,928 --> 00:44:00,846
What now?

657
00:44:00,929 --> 00:44:03,349
Text Director Son Beom-su right now.

658
00:44:03,432 --> 00:44:07,269
"Mr. Son, I'm hungry.
Can you buy me a shrimp pizza?"

659
00:44:07,353 --> 00:44:08,771
Good. That's interesting.

660
00:44:08,854 --> 00:44:10,648
His office is 20 minutes away from here.

661
00:44:10,731 --> 00:44:12,274
It will take 20 minutes to make the pizza.

662
00:44:12,358 --> 00:44:14,860
Considering the time he waits
for the elevator, I'll give you an hour.

663
00:44:14,943 --> 00:44:17,529
Hey, come on. He's a busy person,
planning the drama and everything.

664
00:44:17,613 --> 00:44:19,073
I'm not even sure if he can come.

665
00:44:19,156 --> 00:44:20,908
Gosh, I guess he's not trained yet.

666
00:44:28,457 --> 00:44:29,500
Fine.

667
00:44:38,634 --> 00:44:39,802
I sent it.

668
00:44:39,885 --> 00:44:43,347
Mr. Son, I'm hungry.
Can you buy me a shrimp pizza?

669
00:44:43,430 --> 00:44:45,432
Right now. I need some sugar.

670
00:44:46,642 --> 00:44:48,560
He just read it. He checked the message.

671
00:44:51,772 --> 00:44:53,273
He's ignoring the message?

672
00:44:56,402 --> 00:44:59,905
I'll count an hour
since the moment he read it.

673
00:45:05,077 --> 00:45:06,954
I wanted you to eat something healthy.

674
00:45:07,037 --> 00:45:09,373
So I bought some grilled eel. I didn't...

675
00:45:13,043 --> 00:45:14,878
I didn't know you guys were here.

676
00:45:15,295 --> 00:45:17,005
Nice to meet you. Have you been well?

677
00:45:17,464 --> 00:45:18,966
-Yes.
-Hello.

678
00:46:01,717 --> 00:46:03,635
I guess you just ate it.

679
00:46:03,719 --> 00:46:07,222
Well... It was a thin pizza.
It was too thin.

680
00:46:07,306 --> 00:46:10,851
They want shrimp pizza this time.
We just had bulgogi.

681
00:46:15,272 --> 00:46:16,523
I understand.

682
00:46:17,649 --> 00:46:18,484
I'll go buy one.

683
00:46:18,567 --> 00:46:21,987
No, it's okay. You're here already.
I'll have it delivered.

684
00:46:22,070 --> 00:46:24,490
It will be quicker if I order one
on my way out and pick it up.

685
00:46:24,740 --> 00:46:26,492
Running out of food is a buzzkill.

686
00:46:27,201 --> 00:46:28,410
Eat that while you wait.

687
00:46:28,494 --> 00:46:29,328
Goodness.

688
00:46:30,287 --> 00:46:31,622
You don't have to do that.

689
00:46:36,835 --> 00:46:38,879
Have some. It's grilled eel.

690
00:46:46,220 --> 00:46:48,013
What happened to
objectiveness of existence?

691
00:46:48,096 --> 00:46:51,808
-Just open it.
-It's soup. Open it on the sink.

692
00:46:52,643 --> 00:46:54,728
Why are you yelling at me?

693
00:47:05,989 --> 00:47:08,450
-Well... Hey.
-Yes?

694
00:47:09,409 --> 00:47:11,703
You don't have to stand there like that.

695
00:47:23,006 --> 00:47:24,049
What I mean is,

696
00:47:24,633 --> 00:47:25,634
